               <msContents>
                  <summary>Polemon notifies Herakleides of his arrival in Alexandria, whither he had gone to see the dioiketes on some official matter, and giving an account of subsequent events there.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Recto and verso described</note>
                     <note type="general">Margins (recto): top, 1.7 cm.; left, 2.3 cm.</note>
                     <note type="general">The date is based on the occurrence of Apollonios the Basilikos Grammateus</note>
                     <note type="lines">Recto along the fibers, 2 cols. (57 lines); Verso along the fibers, 7 lines.</note>
                     <note type="paleography">Regular cursive</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">Text written continuously on recto and verso</note>
                     <note type="local_note">1761</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
